      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NAROBI NZ (5) scored again to make it three wins in a row at her latest appearance over 2050m at Port Pirie, getting home by a neck after taking charge a fair way out. Has the talent to take this out. MY ULTIMATE HARRY (1) finished fifth last start over 2050m at Port Pirie but gave a good account, beaten only 2.5 metres. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Meets a comparable field and he can test this line-up. VATICAN GREEN NZ (2) last appeared when he scored by a nose over 1800m at Kapunda five-and-a-half months ago. Should be thereabouts. NANCESTIGER (6) is worth some thought despite his last-start sixth over 2230m at this track on March 11.",
